WEBVTT

00:10.311 --> 00:11.936
Hello, Roz.

00:12.105 --> 00:13.386
l say, hello, Roz.

00:13.565 --> 00:15.143
Oh, l'm sorry.

00:15.318 --> 00:17.774
Oh, don't be.
l didn't mean to disturb your reading.

00:17.946 --> 00:19.939
- Actually, l'm doing a little research.
- Mm-hm.

00:20.116 --> 00:22.025
Um, l have a meeting
with a publisher tomorrow.

00:22.202 --> 00:23.696
l'm thinking of writing
a children's book.

00:23.871 --> 00:24.902
- Really?
- Yeah.

00:25.080 --> 00:27.157
lt's a story my mom made up for me
when l was a kid.

00:27.333 --> 00:28.828
l tell it to Alice all the time now.

00:29.002 --> 00:31.161
l thought it'd be a kick
if l could get it published.

00:31.339 --> 00:34.506
Good for you, Roz. You know,
l've dabbled in juvenile fiction myself.

00:34.885 --> 00:36.925
Yes, Niles and l,
when we were boys,

00:37.096 --> 00:39.884
wrote a series of stories together
in which we were the heroes.

00:40.058 --> 00:43.678
<i>Along the lines of The Hardy Boys
or a Nancy Drew.</i>

00:43.855 --> 00:45.932
<i>The Nancy Boys?</i>

00:48.528 --> 00:50.320
No.

00:51.073 --> 00:53.197
<i>Called The Crane Boys Mysteries.</i>

00:53.368 --> 00:57.319
They were two plucky lads who used
their keen psychological insight

00:57.498 --> 01:00.785
to solve crimes brought home
by their detective father.

01:00.961 --> 01:03.998
- How many of these did you write?
- Thirty-four.

01:04.174 --> 01:08.042
Yes, there was ''The Mystery
of the One-Eared Monkey,''

01:08.221 --> 01:10.677
''On Your Mark, Get Set, Die,''

01:10.849 --> 01:13.602
and there was one
where our father was kidnapped

01:13.770 --> 01:17.519
and the only clue
was a dented Ballantine can.

01:17.691 --> 01:19.934
- ''The Suspicious Six-Pack.''
- Excellent.

01:20.111 --> 01:22.270
- Please, Niles, pull up a chair.
- All right, l will.

01:22.448 --> 01:24.488
l can't stay long though.
Uh, latte to go, please.

01:24.659 --> 01:26.699
l'm on my way to the spa
to pick up Daphne.

01:26.870 --> 01:29.658
Oh, that reminds me, what time
should l be at the apartment tonight?

01:29.832 --> 01:32.834
Oh, well, let's see.
lt's an hour's trip to the spa

01:33.003 --> 01:34.795
and there's a two-hour
graduation ceremony,

01:34.964 --> 01:38.583
at the end of which they all throw
their fat pants into the air.

01:39.095 --> 01:41.135
- Say 7:00.
- Okay, great. l'll see you there.

01:41.306 --> 01:42.469
NlLES: Yes.
- Bye. Bye, Roz.

01:42.641 --> 01:44.515
- Now, speaking of Daphne, ahem,
- Mm-hm.

01:44.685 --> 01:46.346
l was hoping
you could spare her Friday.

01:46.521 --> 01:48.680
l'm planning to take her
on a little getaway weekend,

01:48.857 --> 01:53.521
where l think we may be taking
our relationship to the next level.

01:53.697 --> 01:55.774
Oh, my God, Niles,
you're going to propose?

01:55.950 --> 01:58.276
No, not that level.
The level before that.

01:59.288 --> 02:00.948
You're gonna ask her
to move in with you?

02:01.123 --> 02:03.033
One more level before that.

02:03.627 --> 02:06.119
- Well, you're already dating.
- No, that's two levels.

02:06.297 --> 02:08.455
[lNAUDlBLE DlALOGUE]

02:08.633 --> 02:10.674
Oh, for heaven's sake, just tell me.

02:10.845 --> 02:16.267
Well, you know, we're going
to consummate our relationship.

02:17.896 --> 02:19.521
What?

02:21.108 --> 02:24.810
Well, uh... Gosh, l--
lt's none of my business.

02:24.988 --> 02:27.860
l just thought you'd already
reached that level.

02:28.034 --> 02:29.410
What made you think that?

02:29.578 --> 02:31.571
Ooh, l don't know.
l guess everybody just assumed.

02:31.747 --> 02:33.657
- Who's everybody?
- Nobody.

02:35.544 --> 02:39.412
But, Niles, you have been on
overnight trips together, haven't you?

02:39.591 --> 02:41.335
Well, yes,
but they were perfectly chaste.

02:41.510 --> 02:42.625
Oh.

02:42.803 --> 02:45.046
Daphne wanted to wait
until the time was right.

02:45.223 --> 02:47.596
And, well, we've just both
been missing each other so much

02:47.768 --> 02:51.684
these last few weeks,
l think the time is upon us.

02:51.857 --> 02:54.349
- Oh, l'm happy for you, Niles.
- Thank you.

02:54.527 --> 02:58.478
Gosh, nobody's gonna believe
you two haven't slept together.

02:58.658 --> 03:01.196
- Who's nobody?
- Nobody.

