03:13.344 --> 03:14.624
Oh, hey, l got you something.

03:15.722 --> 03:17.181
Here.

03:19.101 --> 03:22.388
Oh, Niles, it's lovely.

03:22.814 --> 03:24.606
But l already
have a dress like this.

03:24.775 --> 03:25.890
l know. That's it.

03:26.069 --> 03:29.154
That's the dress you wore five years
ago when we danced the tango.

03:30.199 --> 03:31.610
l don't understand.

03:32.243 --> 03:33.572
lt's for this weekend.

03:34.455 --> 03:35.700
Only this time,

03:35.873 --> 03:41.581
instead of ending in heartache,
the evening can end in triumph.

03:42.298 --> 03:46.131
That's very romantic,
but l'm not sure l can fit into it.

03:46.304 --> 03:47.467
Not yet anyway.

03:47.639 --> 03:49.798
Oh, nonsense.
You're as svelte as you ever were.

03:49.975 --> 03:51.256
You're sweet.

03:51.435 --> 03:53.013
lt was cute
when l came out of the spa

03:53.188 --> 03:54.980
and you pretended
you couldn't see me.

03:55.149 --> 03:56.524
Who said that? Who's in my car?

03:56.692 --> 03:59.065
[DAPHNE LAUGHlNG]

03:59.279 --> 04:01.985
Well, you've worked so hard
and you stuck with it.

04:02.158 --> 04:03.950
l want you to know
how proud l am.

04:04.119 --> 04:06.076
Actually, l'm proud of myself.

04:06.246 --> 04:09.498
The staff therapist even
complimented me on my willpower.

04:09.668 --> 04:11.127
Oh, so you did see a therapist?

04:11.295 --> 04:12.754
Yeah, it's all part
of the programme

04:12.922 --> 04:15.046
to help you figure out
the cause of your overeating.

04:15.217 --> 04:18.716
Mm-hm. Well, if you ask me,
it's a classic case of sublimation,

04:18.887 --> 04:21.095
using food as a substitute for sex.

04:21.642 --> 04:23.884
l recommend
you see a certain doctor

04:24.062 --> 04:26.138
l know very well,
he can help you.

04:26.315 --> 04:28.522
Yeah. That's not what Gloria thinks.

04:28.693 --> 04:31.730
- Heh. Gloria?
- The therapist.

04:31.905 --> 04:32.937
Oh.

04:33.115 --> 04:36.735
My patients call me Dr. Crane,
but, uh, whatever.

04:36.912 --> 04:39.748
So, uh, what does Gloria think?

04:39.916 --> 04:41.826
She thinks
l may have gained the weight

04:42.002 --> 04:44.375
as a way to create distance
between us.

04:44.547 --> 04:46.042
Oh. Hmm...

04:46.216 --> 04:48.423
And, uh, why
would you wanna do that?

04:48.802 --> 04:51.674
Well, when you and l
first came together,

04:51.848 --> 04:53.925
we decided to wait
and get to know each other

04:54.101 --> 04:56.675
before bringing the relationship
into the bedroom.

04:57.063 --> 04:59.686
Then as time went on,
you told me all these stories

04:59.859 --> 05:02.018
about how you'd pined for me
for seven years,

05:02.195 --> 05:04.901
how l'd been
your unobtainable dream.

05:05.074 --> 05:07.198
How could anybody
live up to that?

05:08.120 --> 05:10.825
See, Gloria thinks l was terrified
of letting you down,

05:10.998 --> 05:14.000
of not being perfect, so l ate.

05:14.545 --> 05:17.463
And l ate. And apparently ate.

05:17.632 --> 05:19.091
[DAPHNE LAUGHlNG]

05:19.259 --> 05:21.881
Daphne,
you couldn't possibly let me down.

05:22.931 --> 05:25.138
And as for the weight,
it didn't matter.

05:25.309 --> 05:26.554
l never noticed.

05:27.103 --> 05:30.520
That's another thing.
l gained 60 pounds.

05:30.691 --> 05:32.815
Don't you think it's strange
you couldn't see it?

05:32.986 --> 05:35.477
No, it's not strange. l love you.

05:35.864 --> 05:37.941
And l love you too.

05:40.245 --> 05:41.823
You know what Gloria says?

05:43.458 --> 05:44.952
No.

05:45.127 --> 05:47.001
She says
you couldn't see the extra weight

05:47.171 --> 05:49.164
because you're only seeing
the perfect me

05:49.340 --> 05:51.630
you've carried around
in your head for seven years.

05:51.802 --> 05:54.590
She calls it
''looking through love goggles.''

05:55.640 --> 05:57.550
Alrighty, let's get her on the phone,
shall we?

05:57.727 --> 06:00.016
Niles, don't.
l'm not trying to upset you.

06:00.188 --> 06:02.894
l'm just telling you
what we discussed in therapy.

06:03.067 --> 06:05.144
l understand, l understand.

06:05.320 --> 06:08.571
And l know how much
you've looked forward to this weekend,

06:08.741 --> 06:12.822
but until l sort this out, l may need
a little more time before l'm--

06:12.997 --> 06:14.028
Absolutely. Say no more.

06:14.207 --> 06:16.912
We can easily postpone
the weekend.

06:18.504 --> 06:21.956
Of course, if my theory is correct and
you are eating as a substitute for sex,

06:22.134 --> 06:23.593
then you're taking a terrible risk.

06:23.761 --> 06:25.220
[NlLES lMlTATES EXPLOSlON
AND DAPHNE LAUGHS]

06:25.388 --> 06:27.962
l know, huh?

06:30.269 --> 06:32.393
l love you, Niles.

06:32.898 --> 06:35.021
l love you too.

06:37.362 --> 06:39.569
[FOOTSTEPS]

06:39.740 --> 06:42.314
MARTlN: Roz, you know,
if you really wanna do a kid's book,

06:42.494 --> 06:43.953
you ought to write one
about Eddie.

06:44.121 --> 06:47.289
- l'd buy one about Eddie.
- Thanks, but l already have an idea.

06:47.459 --> 06:50.496
Besides, if l was gonna use a dog,
l'd probably use my own.

06:50.671 --> 06:53.507
Well, you wanna make your dog happy
or you wanna sell books?

06:53.675 --> 06:56.345
Now, l was thinking,
Eddie joins the circus.

06:56.512 --> 06:59.004
And he has all this clown makeup on
and everything, you know.

06:59.182 --> 07:00.297
And he juggles and stuff.

07:00.476 --> 07:02.968
And then you could do one
where he invents this flying machine

07:03.146 --> 07:05.519
and has all these wacky adventures.

07:05.691 --> 07:07.150
That's kind of cute.

07:07.318 --> 07:09.110
He could join a flock of geese

07:09.279 --> 07:13.610
or he could become
the world's first dog traffic reporter.

07:14.077 --> 07:16.284
Eddie would never do that.

07:16.455 --> 07:19.291
You really don't get Eddie, do you?

07:19.459 --> 07:20.491
[DOOR OPENS]

07:20.961 --> 07:23.453
- Hey, look who's home.
MARTlN: Hey.

07:23.882 --> 07:26.967
- ls this all for me?
- Oh, Daphne. God, we missed you.

07:27.136 --> 07:29.176
- You look great, Daphne.
- Thank you, Roz.

07:29.347 --> 07:30.806
MARTlN:
Great? You look fantastic.

07:30.974 --> 07:33.893
l don't know what they did to you there,
but what a difference.

07:34.062 --> 07:36.055
Yes, l was getting pretty big,
wasn't l?

07:36.231 --> 07:38.438
Big? You were ginormous.

07:38.609 --> 07:40.021
FRASlER:
Dad.

07:40.195 --> 07:42.188
- l'm telling her how good she looks.
- Yes, yes.

07:42.364 --> 07:44.821
- Come here, old man.
- You really do look lovely, Daphne.

07:44.993 --> 07:48.694
Oh, thank you, Dr. Crane.
But l still have to be careful what l eat.

07:48.873 --> 07:50.284
Yes, of course. And to that end,

07:50.458 --> 07:52.784
l have a little surprise for you
in the refrigerator.

07:52.961 --> 07:54.587
You didn't have to do that.

07:54.756 --> 07:56.583
lt's not some of those
low-cal dinners, is it?

07:56.758 --> 07:57.921
FRASlER:
Just go look.

07:58.093 --> 07:59.125
[LAUGHS]

07:59.303 --> 08:01.510
[SQUEALlNG]

08:04.018 --> 08:05.892
That's hysterical.

08:06.062 --> 08:08.518
lt's called the Refrigerator Pig.
lt's a little plastic pig.

08:08.691 --> 08:10.102
He's got a recording in his belly.

08:10.276 --> 08:11.936
Every time you open
the refrigerator door,

08:12.112 --> 08:13.654
you'll hear his scolding squeal.

08:14.490 --> 08:16.282
So, Daphne,
tell us about the spa.

08:16.451 --> 08:18.195
Well, it was lots of hard work.

08:18.370 --> 08:21.822
We had hikes every morning
and sessions with a personal trainer.

08:22.000 --> 08:25.251
And a wonderful therapist.
You're gonna love this.

08:27.757 --> 08:30.130
Yes, there was a professional
therapist on staff.

08:30.302 --> 08:32.544
Mm-hm. Named Gloria.

08:32.722 --> 08:34.799
Who helped me dig down
to the root of my problems.

08:34.975 --> 08:36.967
Yes, Gloria's very handy
with a shovel.

08:37.145 --> 08:38.176
[LAUGHS]

08:38.897 --> 08:41.684
Well, she must have been very good.
l mean, obviously, look at you.

08:41.859 --> 08:45.312
Well, Gloria's very empathetic because
she had a similar weight problem.

08:45.489 --> 08:47.482
Only she didn't have anyone
to help deal with it.

08:47.658 --> 08:49.367
She had to battle it alone for years.

08:49.536 --> 08:51.660
She didn't have a boyfriend
she could blame?

08:53.124 --> 08:55.164
ls there something
you want to say to me?

08:55.460 --> 08:56.789
No.

08:56.962 --> 09:01.008
Well, l've got something to say.
l would like to propose a toast.

09:01.176 --> 09:03.335
l was very lucky
to have someone like Gloria.

09:03.513 --> 09:07.642
Yes. You usually have to go all the way
to a hair salon for that kind of insight.

09:08.644 --> 09:10.685
NlLES: Here, l'll take that.
FRASlER: Yes, uh...

09:10.856 --> 09:15.151
Well, uh, Daphne, the important thing
is that you're feeling better

09:15.320 --> 09:17.562
and that you're back home
where you belong.

09:17.740 --> 09:20.148
MARTlN: Right.
- l better make mine water.

09:20.326 --> 09:22.735
Champagne is pure sugar,
you know.

09:24.165 --> 09:25.743
Niles, what the hell
is wrong with you?

09:25.917 --> 09:29.121
Oh, Frasier, you would not believe
the hack psychobabble

09:29.297 --> 09:31.124
this woman
has filled Daphne's head with.

09:31.299 --> 09:33.873
Well, even if that's true,
that's no reason to act like an ass.

09:34.053 --> 09:36.971
Now, you just shape up
and treat Daphne with respect.

09:37.140 --> 09:38.801
[SQUEALlNG]

09:43.649 --> 09:44.680
DAPHNE:
Ooh...

09:45.276 --> 09:49.275
Apparently that pig of yours
can dish it out, but he can't take it.

09:51.075 --> 09:53.649
- So how about that toast?
- Oh, good idea.

09:53.829 --> 09:55.027
FRASlER:
Right, uh...

09:55.206 --> 09:56.581
To Daphne.

09:56.749 --> 10:01.876
Your warmth and spirit
have helped make this place a home.

10:02.048 --> 10:06.261
Your influence can be seen
in a thousand different ways.

10:06.429 --> 10:08.588
Unless, of course,
one's wearing his love goggles.

10:08.765 --> 10:11.304
That's it.
Niles, l think you should go.

10:11.853 --> 10:15.020
- What?
- l want you to leave right now.

10:37.845 --> 10:41.215
Nice call on the Refrigerator Pig.

10:48.484 --> 10:50.193
So you don't think
l have a germ phobia?

10:50.362 --> 10:53.862
Not at all. Just a healthy sense
of personal hygiene.

10:54.033 --> 10:57.569
Ah. Here is the number of the man
who cleans my telephones.

10:57.746 --> 11:00.997
There you go. The best in Seattle.
Now, you take care.

11:01.168 --> 11:04.039
No, don't touch, don't touch.
There you go.

11:04.756 --> 11:08.457
Frasier.
Uh, what are you doing here?

11:08.636 --> 11:12.717
Oh, l just wanted to see
how you were doing after last night.

11:12.891 --> 11:14.849
Daphne caught me up
on what's been going on.

11:15.019 --> 11:19.184
Oh, wonderful. So she's talking to
every therapist under the sun but me.

11:19.525 --> 11:21.352
She said she tried to talk to you.

11:21.528 --> 11:23.984
No, she tried to blame me.

11:24.156 --> 11:27.075
According to
her puppet master, Gloria,

11:27.243 --> 11:29.071
Daphne overate
because she was afraid

11:29.246 --> 11:32.497
she couldn't live up
to my image of her.

11:33.001 --> 11:36.086
- Well, there may be something to that.
- Oh--

11:36.297 --> 11:41.210
She does have seven years
of fantasy to live up to.

11:41.387 --> 11:42.965
What fantasy?

11:43.139 --> 11:45.263
l have a very realistic picture
of Daphne.

11:45.434 --> 11:48.851
l love her for who she is.
l have since the very beginning.

11:49.022 --> 11:52.357
All right, when exactly was the very
beginning for the two of you anyway?

11:52.527 --> 11:56.573
Well, don't you remember?
You introduced us.

11:56.741 --> 11:59.696
Daphne, this is my brother, Niles.

12:01.288 --> 12:03.910
- You're Daphne?
- Why, yes, l am.

12:04.251 --> 12:07.371
Well, when Frasier told me
he'd hired an Englishwoman,

12:07.547 --> 12:11.248
l pictured someone a little more--
Not quite so--

12:11.427 --> 12:13.219
You're Daphne?

12:13.388 --> 12:15.796
- Right again. lt's nice to meet you.
- Look at you, Niles.

12:15.974 --> 12:19.225
The woman's a stranger to you and yet
you're ready to hand her your heart.

12:19.395 --> 12:23.311
Well, l may have been a tad smitten.
What's your point?

12:23.484 --> 12:26.985
My point is... Niles, pay attention.

12:27.489 --> 12:29.815
My point is, your so-called
realistic picture of Daphne

12:29.993 --> 12:33.327
has been clouded from the start
by your intense attraction to her.

12:33.497 --> 12:37.331
All right. Perhaps at the beginning
l was blinded by infatuation.

12:37.503 --> 12:40.173
But over the years,
l've learned everything about her.

12:40.340 --> 12:42.084
And my love has only deepened.

12:42.259 --> 12:46.472
l've learned that she's caring
and compassionate. Uh...

12:46.640 --> 12:49.013
And she can be moody sometimes.

12:49.810 --> 12:53.856
She likes jelly on her pancakes
instead of syrup. Uh...

12:54.066 --> 12:57.270
Her laugh, it's like music.

12:57.446 --> 13:00.151
Oh, and that girl can dance.

13:00.324 --> 13:02.116
You're beautiful. You're a goddess.

13:02.285 --> 13:04.907
Oh, l don't ever want
this moment to end.

13:05.081 --> 13:06.112
Then let's not let it.

13:06.290 --> 13:08.082
NlLES:
This is one of my favourite memories.

13:08.251 --> 13:10.624
See, that's the dress
l wanted her to wear this weekend.

13:10.796 --> 13:12.588
lsn't she spectacular?

13:12.757 --> 13:14.086
FRASlER:
lndeed she is.

13:14.259 --> 13:17.427
