Oh, wait, look at this. Watch.

13:19.600 --> 13:21.142
[CROWD GASPlNG]

13:21.310 --> 13:22.888
l come here often.

13:23.063 --> 13:25.471
l suspect a part of you
has never left.

13:25.649 --> 13:27.358
Can you blame me? Look at us.

13:27.527 --> 13:31.063
We're magnificent together.
We're moving in perfect sync.

13:31.240 --> 13:33.114
There's that word perfect again.

13:33.994 --> 13:35.322
l know what you're thinking.

13:35.496 --> 13:38.497
Just because this evening was perfect
doesn't mean l'm idealising Daphne.

13:38.666 --> 13:40.992
Did you hear yourself out there?
You called her a goddess.

13:41.170 --> 13:42.962
You can't build
a higher pedestal than that.

13:43.131 --> 13:45.753
Who could possibly compete
with that sort of image?

13:47.553 --> 13:50.638
That's not fair. l'm well aware
that's just one side of her.

13:50.807 --> 13:54.758
l'm also acquainted with her
ordinary, domestic, everyday side.

13:54.938 --> 13:58.272
[HUMMlNG]

13:58.442 --> 14:01.978
<i>Heart and soul
l fell in love with you</i>

14:02.156 --> 14:05.573
<i>Heart and soul
The way a fool would do...</i>

14:06.161 --> 14:07.905
- Oh, please.
- What?

14:08.080 --> 14:10.287
Even your everyday memories
are idealised.

14:10.458 --> 14:13.211
How long until the cartoon bluebird
lands on her shoulder?

14:13.379 --> 14:18.089
All right, so maybe my memories
of Daphne are perfect.

14:18.260 --> 14:22.758
Did it ever occur to you
that perhaps Daphne just is perfect?

14:22.933 --> 14:24.642
<i>BOTH:
Because you held me tight</i>

